==English==
===Noun===
An '''overdraft''' occurs when an attempt is made to [[draw]] more [[Finance|funds]] from an [[account]] than that account has at the time.  The most common usage is in the context of [[Bank|banking]] where the funds are monetary and the account is a monetary repository held by the bank on behalf of a bank customer.

===Etymology===
Overdraft is a [[Portmanteau_word|portmanteau]] of [[over]] (with respect to available funds) and [[draft]] (in the sense of a request for funds).